This paper deals with analyzing network traffic to identify user information, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to classify the traffic, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential privacy implications of the identified information, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
